<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1658] Negative query weirdness</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1658</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the standard Solr example, the queries&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adapter AND NOT power&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;adapter AND (NOT power)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;are different.  The second will never return any results.  I find this surprising.  I think the second query should be the same as the first.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
