                            <comment id="12790930" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Tue, 15 Dec 2009 20:09:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree.  Extended dismax already implements this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It comes down to needing a flag... sometimes you want pure negative queries (when parsing query parts for example) and sometimes you don&apos;t.  We should just add a boolean flag to SolrQueryParser.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;But&lt;/b&gt; we don&apos;t want to do this for the top level for filter queries - as an optimization, solr currently caches -foo:x the same as foo:x and if we always handled negative queries at the QP level, it would disable that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16067426" author="janhoy" created="Wed, 28 Jun 2017 23:10:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This oold issue can be reproduced with &quot;lucene&quot; qparser in 6.6. On techproducts example the query &lt;tt&gt;adapter AND (NOT dock)&lt;/tt&gt; fails while &lt;tt&gt;adapter AND NOT dock&lt;/tt&gt; succeeds.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
